<subSubSection id="35B000D8EABFED069D8A3D8B480D1901" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="013B99A49AE1165A3CE9537781F2348B" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="869D09A87869CDC8F4644665D00F9560" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName id="393B62EBDB41BD2272695AC5D8814E48" authorityName="Refulio" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Tovar" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa gigantea" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis id="246E47EDB18C97DAA5A88137490BFAB6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Poa gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Tovar) Refulio in having glumes 3/4 to 7/8 as long as the adjacent lemmas (versus glumes about as long or longer than the adjacent lemma), a callus with a sparse, short, dorsal tuft of woolly hairs (versus no web), culms 50-72 cm tall (versus 22-58 cm tall) and spikelets 4.1-4.8 mm long (versus 5-5.5 mm long).
</paragraph>
